x
y=1-x+\frac{x^2}{2!}-\frac{x^3}{3!}+\dots
z=-y-\frac{y^2}{2}-\frac{y^3}{3}-\dots
\ln (\frac{1}{1-e^z})
y=e^{-x}
z=\ln {(1-y)}
z=\ln(1-e^{-x})
z=\log(1-e^{-x})
\log\left(\frac{1}{1-e^{z}}\right)=\log\left(\frac{1}{1-e^{\log(1-e^{-x})}}\right)= \log\left(\frac{1}{1-(1-e^{-x})}\right)= \log\left(\frac{1}{e^{-x}}\right)=\log e^x=x 
